00:45:35.675 --> 00:45:37.220
and it becomes public entity.

00:45:37.220 --> 00:45:39.830
You find it a little bit more
difficult to take pictures now?

00:45:39.830 --> 00:45:41.580
Or is it just because
photos are so common

00:45:41.580 --> 00:45:44.512
now that people are desensitized
to others taking photos?

00:45:44.512 --> 00:45:46.970
RICK SMOLAN: I'm going to answer
your question a little bit

00:45:46.970 --> 00:45:49.290
differently, because
I'm thinking about this.

00:45:49.290 --> 00:45:50.760
Some of you may
remember the time

00:45:50.760 --> 00:45:53.220
where it was a novel
idea to actually put

00:45:53.220 --> 00:45:54.742
a modem in a computer.

00:45:54.742 --> 00:45:56.200
Like, gee, you mean
computers might

00:45:56.200 --> 00:45:57.700
want to actually
talk to each other?

00:45:57.700 --> 00:46:00.013
And you'd actually have a
separate 300-baud modem,

00:46:00.013 --> 00:46:02.570
and it would make this
[SCREECHING] noise.

00:46:02.570 --> 00:46:07.485
And the first time someone
said to me "always on"-- like,

00:46:07.485 --> 00:46:09.360
you would have a Wi-Fi
network in your house,

00:46:09.360 --> 00:46:10.497
and you wouldn't dial in.

00:46:10.497 --> 00:46:12.205
You wouldn't turn the
internet on or off.

00:46:12.205 --> 00:46:13.540
It would always be on.

00:46:13.540 --> 00:46:15.630
It's like, why would you
want it to always be on?

00:46:15.630 --> 00:46:17.330
What would you
possibly do with it?

00:46:17.330 --> 00:46:19.600
Well, this actually
correlates to Google Glass.

00:46:19.600 --> 00:46:21.558
And some of the things
I've been thinking about

00:46:21.558 --> 00:46:23.180
is, what if we start
wearing devices

00:46:23.180 --> 00:46:25.330
that record everything in 360?

00:46:25.330 --> 00:46:28.450
There's a company here in New
York called [? Bemuse ?] that

00:46:28.450 --> 00:46:32.150
has a football helmet with
a little bubble on top.

00:46:32.150 --> 00:46:34.890
And literally as the guys
are running down the field,

00:46:34.890 --> 00:46:35.740
it's not spinning.

00:46:35.740 --> 00:46:37.700
It's actually reporting in 360.

00:46:37.700 --> 00:46:39.980
And then you at home
can sit there and decide

00:46:39.980 --> 00:46:41.760
if you want to look to the
right or the left to the player,

00:46:41.760 --> 00:46:43.210
either in real
time or afterwards.

00:46:43.210 --> 00:46:44.820
So I'm wondering
what the world's

00:46:44.820 --> 00:46:46.760
like, just the way that
it seemed odd to me

00:46:46.760 --> 00:46:48.540
that you'd want
always-on internet.

00:46:48.540 --> 00:46:50.850
What if, as we all
walk around, there's

00:46:50.850 --> 00:46:54.050
this 360 degrees
sphere of recording

00:46:54.050 --> 00:46:56.510
where a year from now,
somebody could literally

00:46:56.510 --> 00:46:58.260
fly from one side of
the room to the other

00:46:58.260 --> 00:47:01.020
just by going through this
sphere around that was recorded

00:47:01.020 --> 00:47:02.180
around, where it's free?

00:47:02.180 --> 00:47:02.940
It's ubiquitous.

00:47:02.940 --> 00:47:04.270
It's everywhere.

00:47:04.270 --> 00:47:06.247
And what does that
do to privacy?

